14/03/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The leaders of the ruling coalition agreed Thursday (13 March) to step up efforts to resolve remaining differences and speed up implementation of the Ohrid peace accord.
Branko Crvenkovski of the Social Democratic Alliance of Macedonia, Risto Penov of the Liberal Democratic Party and Ali Ahmeti of the Democratic Union for Integration reached preliminary agreement on problems stemming from the use of the Albanian language on new Macedonian passports and driving licences, as well as during parliamentary commission sessions.
The leaders also agreed to accept the results of the 2002 census, scheduled for release soon.
(Utrinski Vesnik, Dnevnik - 14/03/03;
A1 TV - 13/03/03)
